text:
Technical Data on Service Sector – Office Depot, American Airlines Group, Starbucks, Pandora Media and American Eagle Outfitters  
ACI Association has initiated research coverage on the following equities: Office Depot, Inc. , American Airlines Group, Inc. , Starbucks Corporation , Pandora Media, Inc. American Eagle Outfitters, Inc. . On Monday, September 21, 2015, NASDAQ ended at 4,828.95, up 0.04%, Dow Jones advanced 0.77%, to finish the day at 16,510.19, and the S&P closed at 1,966.97, up 0.46%. Register for your complimentary reports at the links given below.
—
Office Depot Inc. 
—
Office Depot Inc.’s stock edged lower by 2.39% to close Monday’s session at USD 7.36. The company’s shares oscillated between USD 7.36 and USD 7.63 in trade during the day. The stock recorded a trading volume of 7.19 million shares, which was below its 50-day daily average volume of 8.37 million shares and below its 52-week average volume of 9.90 million shares. Over the last three days Office Depot Inc.’s shares have declined by 1.60% and in the past one week the stock has moved down 0.14%. Furthermore, over the last three months the stock has lost 18.67% and in the past six months the shares have shed 21.66%. On a compounded total return basis, the company stock has given a negative return of 2.77% in the last month whilst generating a positive return of 33.09% in the past year.
—
American Airlines Group Inc. 
—
The stock of American Airlines Group Inc. lost 0.60% to close Monday’s session at USD 43.23. The shares of the company moved in the range of USD 42.88 and USD 44.01. A trading volume of 6.69 million shares was recorded, which was lower than its 150-day daily average volume of 12.63 million shares and below its 52-week average volume of 13.41 million shares. Over the last five days, American Airlines Group Inc.’s shares have advanced 2.22%. Additionally, in the past six months the shares have registered a loss of 20.53%. The company has returned 8.75% in the past one month and 4.26% in the last three months, on a compounded total return basis. American Airlines Group Inc. has a current dividend yield of 0.92%.
